Gulf oil spill. These avoidable disasters reveal the interdependency of people and machines within systems whose complex behavior was undreamt of by their designers, until it was too late. Petroski shows that even the simplest technology is embedded in cultural and socioeconomic constraints, complications, and contradictions.Failure to imagine the possibility of failure is the most profound mistake engineers can make. Software developers realized this early on and looked outside their young field, to structural engineering, as they sought a historical perspective to help them identify their own potential mistakes. By explaining the interconnectedness of technology and culture and the dangers that can emerge from complexity, Petroski demonstrates that we would all do well to follow their lead.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aIngenieurwissenschaften und Maschinenbau. 0aStructural engineering. 0aStructural failures. 0aSystem failures (Engineering). 7aSCIENCE / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE MATHEMATICS, PHYSICS, ENGINEERING 2012z9783110293722oZDB-23-DMI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET MATHEMATIK, PHYSIK, INGENIEURWISS. 2012z9783110288926oZDB-23-DMP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013 (Canada)z978311075606708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHarvard University Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044220540uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.978067406543740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674065437423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780674065437.jpg  a978-3-11-044220-5  Harvard University Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-